<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP">
    <summary>
      <para>Identifies the stencil operations that can be performed during depth-stencil testing.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This enum is used by the <see cref="D3D12_DEPTH_STENCILOP_DESC" /> structure.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/cd3dx12-depth-stencil-desc">CD3DX12_DEPTH_STENCIL_DESC</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/direct3d-12-enumerations">Core enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_KEEP">
    <summary>
      <para>Keep the existing stencil data.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_ZERO">
    <summary>
      <para>Set the stencil data to 0.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_REPLACE">
    <summary>
      <para>Set the stencil data to the reference value set by calling <see cref="ID3D12GraphicsCommandList.OMSetStencilRef" />.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_INCR_SAT">
    <summary>
      <para>Increment the stencil value by 1, and clamp the result.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_DECR_SAT">
    <summary>
      <para>Decrement the stencil value by 1, and clamp the result.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_INVERT">
    <summary>
      <para>Invert the stencil data.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_INCR">
    <summary>
      <para>Increment the stencil value by 1, and wrap the result if necessary.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_STENCIL_OP.D3D12_STENCIL_OP_DECR">
    <summary>
      <para>Decrement the stencil value by 1, and wrap the result if necessary.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>